	abstract = {The concluding chapter summarizes the major cross-cutting issues surrounding algorithmic nudging. It spotlights ethical, moral, and philosophical underpinnings of the practice of behavioral nudging and what these issues portend for the future as technology and consumer psychology advance. Comparative points of the individual contributors are discussed by the editors which provides insight on the advantages as well as risks of using algorithmic nudging via communication channels. Integrating the major themes of philosophy and praxis, the editors combine insights from the individual chapters. Drawing attention to the importance of having an overarching architectonic at both the moral and procedural levels, the editors contend that having such a framework will be necessary to foster an intellectual climate that protects human autonomy. Their argument has particular pertinence as the power of artificial intelligence (AI) seeps ever deeper into societal structures. The theme of concern about the seemingly unlimited power of nudging by often imperceptible levels of control is magnified by AI. Outstanding examples of just how intimate nudging can become are the ever-proliferating uses of chatbots and large language models such as ChatGPT. As people use these machine learning technologies, behavioral data can be accumulated that touches on every aspect of life. Thus an enduring challenge remains how to encourage and direct beneficial technological innovations while also protecting individual autonomy and preventing exploitation. © The Editor(s) (if applicable) and The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2023.},
