	abstract = {The use of artificial intelligence (AI) in language learning is growing, with the potential to offer personalized and adaptive learning experiences, provide immediate feedback, and enhance students’ learning outcomes. A meta-analysis of 20 studies published between 2015 and 2022 investigated the impact of AI-based language learning tools on language proficiency, motivation, and engagement. The findings suggest that these tools have a positive effect on language learning outcomes, with moderate to large effect sizes (0.58, 0.44, and 0.44, respectively). The meta-analysis included studies that evaluated the impact of AI-based language learning tools on a variety of language learning outcomes, including vocabulary acquisition, grammar knowledge, listening comprehension, speaking fluency, and writing skills. The results of the meta-analysis showed that AI-based language learning tools had a positive effect on all of these outcomes. The findings of this meta-analysis have important implications for language teachers and instructional designers. These findings suggest that AI-based language learning tools can be an effective way to improve language proficiency, motivation, and engagement among students. These tools have the potential to offer personalized and adaptive learning experiences, which can help address individual student needs and preferences. Additionally, they can provide immediate feedback and opportunities for practice, which can enhance students’ learning outcomes. However, it is important to note that the studies included in this meta-analysis varied in quality, with some studies having small sample sizes or limited control groups. Additionally, some studies only focused on specific aspects of language learning, such as vocabulary acquisition or pronunciation, rather than overall language proficiency. Further research is needed to better understand the specific mechanisms by which AI-based language learning tools improve language learning outcomes and to explore potential drawbacks or limitations of these tools. Overall, the findings of this meta-analysis suggest that AI-based language learning tools have the potential to enhance language learning outcomes, particularly in terms of language proficiency, motivation, and engagement. These findings have important implications for language teachers and instructional designers, who may consider incorporating AIbased tools into their language learning curricula to enhance student learning outcomes. © 2024 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
