nt degrees of renal damage, while cR2⁎ and mFF values showed moderate diagnostic efficacy. When combining the APT, R2⁎, and FF values, the diagnostic efficiency was significantly improved. Conclusion: mDIXON-Quant combined APTw imaging can be used for improved diagnosis of CKD. © 2023 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
